    <title>Environmental complexity</title>


    <para>The environmental factors take into account the skills profile and experience of the team
        the stability of the requirements and implementation technology factors. The use case points
        method assigns the following weightings to these:
    </para>
    <table>
        <title>Environmental factor weightings</title>
        <tgroup cols="3">
            <thead>
                <row>
                    <entry>
                        <para>Environmental factor</para>
                    </entry>
                    <entry>
                        <para>Weight</para>
                    </entry>
                    <entry>
                        <para>value</para>
                    </entry>
                </row>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <row>
                    <entry>
                        <para>Stable requirements</para>
                    </entry>
                    <entry>
                        <para>2</para>
                    </entry>
                    <entry>
                        <para> </para>
                    </entry>
                </row>

                <row>
                    <entry>
                        <para>Experience in the development process used
                        </para>
                    </entry>
                    <entry>
                        <para>1.5</para>
                    </entry>
                    <entry>
                        <para> </para>
                    </entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>
                        <para>Application experience</para>
                    </entry>
                    <entry>
                        <para>0.5</para>
                    </entry>
                    <entry>
                        <para> </para>
                    </entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>
