        </tgroup>
    </table>
    <note>
        <para>
            For experience in the development process used, the actual weight
            may be adjusted to the <emphasis>type</emphasis> of development process used -
            Lightweight processes like Extreme Programming may be assigned a lower weight.
        </para>
    </note>
    <para>The environmental factor,<literal>EF</literal>, is now calculated as
        <programlisting>
            EF = 1.4 - 0.03 x sum_environmentalFactors (factorWeight x factorValue)
        </programlisting>
    </para>
    <para>A neutral environmental factor would result in a value of 1. If the environment poses
        above average challenges, the value will be larger than one.
    </para>
